    <p>We use black for headings and the main body copy and grey 1 for secondary text.</p>
    <p>We use grey 2, 3 and 4 for borders.</p>
    <p>We use grey 5 as a background tint. This is because:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>it reduces overall page glare</li>
      <li>the <a href="https://www.bdadyslexia.org.uk/employer/dyslexia-style-guide-2018-creating-dyslexia-friendly-content">British Dyslexia Association</a> recommends dark text on a light, but not white, background</li>
      <li>components with important information, like callouts, stand out</li>
    </ul>
    <p>See <a href="/service-manual/styles-components-patterns/colour#colours-in-context">colours in context on this page</a> for more uses of these colours and specific Sass codes.</p>
